            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> the _first_ TUI to attach should maybe try to determine the initial value of `termguicolors`\r\n\r\nOne could argue that `--remote-ui` is a kind of special case which should handle that, since the `nvim_ui_attach` options (`:help ui-option`) are not easy(?) to set from `--remote-ui`.\r\n\r\nOTOH, this really seems like a special case. If a headless server is running, that implies that arbitrary clients are expected to attach and detach. Having special handling for the \"first client\" case seems pretty random.\r\n\r\nIn any case, it seems like `--remote-ui` clients don't have a way to call `nvim_ui_set_option()` or some other way to set UI options. That seems like something we need.",
